# Frontend Performance

## Bundle & Rendering

- Keep client component trees small — push data fetching and static markup to server components
- Split large client islands with `dynamic(() => import(...), { loading: () => <Skeleton /> })`
- Don't import server-only modules into `"use client"` files

## Images & Media

- `next/image` with explicit `width`/`height` (or `fill` + sized parent) to prevent CLS
- Compress assets in `public/`; prefer modern formats (WebP, AVIF) for photos
- Videos: `preload="metadata"`, poster image, lazy load below the fold

## Fonts

- Use `next/font` (already configured) — never load Google Fonts via `<link>` tags

## Checklist Before Shipping UI

- [ ] No layout shift on load (images sized, fonts preloaded)
- [ ] Lighthouse: accessible names, contrast, tap targets
- [ ] Works at 320px and 1440px widths
- [ ] Dark mode consistent if enabled
